🚩 Red flags to evaluate if a friendship is worth fighting for: ☎️ Lack of Reciprocity Your friend fails to show genuine interest in your life, always steering conversations back to themselves without allowing space for you to share your thoughts and experiences. 🎀 One-Sided Effort You’re consistently putting in more effort to maintain the friendship than the other person. 🌘 Negative impact on well-being Being around your friend consistently leaves you feeling drained and stressed, rather than supported and uplifted. 🧿Insecurity and jealousy Persistent feelings of insecurity and jealousy where they constantly compare themselves to you or downplay your achievements. 💥Toxic behaviour Your friend exhibits toxic behaviour such as manipulation, gaslighting, or constant negativity that affects your well-being. 🌬️Growing apart People change and grow over time.If you find you no longer share common interests and values it might be a sign that the friendship has sadly run its course. 🍒 One thing I keep hearing is “I’ve know her for so long”… Bestie! Holding on to a friendship just because you’ve known them forever is not a reason. Letting go of a friendship should be based on your own well-being and what feels healthy and fulfilling. Trust your instincts and prioritize your mental and emotional health in any relationship.
